1. Which role is most critical when building your innovation team?
Solution : B. The Spiritual champion-accountable for driving your end-to-end innovation project with passion

2. What is the purpose of an executive sponsor?
Solution : C. To serve as the senior-most champion, driving engagement and adoption of your project

3. Intrapreneurs drive…
Solution : A. Impact within their organization, wielding their enterpreneurial prowess to seed, grow, and advance innovation

4. Which of these behaviors is a natural part of an innovator's DNA?
Solution : D. Challenging invisible orthodoxies to see beyond the status quo

5. Failure is a normal part of the innovation process—so how can you avoid sweating it when it happens?
Solution : A. Align with management on the intentions and learning goals of your project and celebrate failures as valuable experiences along the way
